  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fractures of the proximal interphalangeal joints continue to pose significant management
      challenges. Thus the aim of our study is to compare two dynamic finger joint distractors
      (Litos® and Ligamentotaxor®) in respect to the radiological standard follow-up examination
      and functional assessments.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
